ovements, and labor movements in Greece, Germany, Spain, Portugal, and Turkey. Contributors discuss municipal campaigns based in popular assemblies, solidarity economies, and independent political organizations fighting for racial, gender, and economic justice in cities such as Jackson, Vancouver, and Newcastle. This volume also studies the lessons learned from the Pink Tide in Latin America as well as the social movements of racialized and gendered workers transforming human rights across the United States. Finally, the book offers case studies from around the world surveying the role of state workers and public sector unions in radically democratizing public administration through coalitions between the providers and users of public services.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aCapitalismxPolitical aspectsvCase studies. 0aLeft-wing extremistsvCase studies. 0aNew LeftvCase studies. 0aRight and left (Political science)vCase studies. 4aCriminology : Criminology. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 4aHistory : Social and Cultural History. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Science. 4aPublic Policy : Public Policy. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political ideologies / Democracy.2bisacsh1 aAkuno, Kali, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aAlbo, Greg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChiasson-LeBel, Thomas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFindlay, Tammy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGray, Paul Christopher, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGray, Paul Christopher, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLafrance, Xavier, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLovell, George I., econtribut